  "text": "# Chromium Renderer Process Sandbox Security Audit\n\n## Summary\nAudited the security sandbox implementation for Chromium's renderer processes across Linux and Windows platforms.\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### 1. Linux Sandbox Base Policy (seccomp-BPF)\nThe Linux sandbox uses a two-layer approach:\n\n**Base Layer**: `sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf-helpers/baseline_policy.h`\n- **Class**: `BaselinePolicy` (extends `bpf_dsl::Policy`)\n- **Purpose**: Implements the foundational seccomp-BPF policy that blocks dangerous syscalls\n- **Key Method**: `EvaluateSyscall(int system_call_number)` - evaluates syscall access\n- **Note**: This is the core seccomp-BPF baseline used across all Linux sandboxes\n\n**Policy Wrapper Layer**: `sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_base_policy_linux.h`\n- **Class**: `BPFBasePolicy` (extends `bpf_dsl::Policy`)\n- **Purpose**: Wraps `BaselinePolicy` for use in the policy framework\n- **Contains**: `std::unique_ptr<BaselinePolicy> baseline_policy_`\n\n**Renderer-Specific Policy**: `sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_renderer_policy_linux.h`\n- **Class**: `RendererProcessPolicy` (extends `BPFBasePolicy`)\n- **Purpose**: Implements renderer-specific restrictions on top of the base policy\n- **Used For**: Renderer and worker processes\n\n### 2. Windows Sandbox Policy\nFile: `sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy_base.h`\n- **Main Class**: `PolicyBase` (line 165) - extends `TargetPolicy`\n- **Configuration Class**: `ConfigBase` (line 47) - extends `TargetConfig`\n- **Purpose**: Defines Windows-specific sandbox policy configuration\n- **Key Methods**:\n  - `SetTokenLevel(TokenLevel initial, TokenLevel lockdown)` - configures process tokens\n  - `SetJobLevel(JobLevel job_level, uint32_t ui_exceptions)` - configures job objects\n  - `AllowFileAccess()`, `SetProcessMitigations()`, etc. - granular policy rules\n- **Related Definition**: `sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy.h` defines the `TargetConfig` interface\n\n### 3. Renderer Process Sandbox Launch Configuration\nFile: `content/browser/renderer_host/renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.h`\n- **Main Class**: `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate`\n- **Extends**: `SandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate`\n- **Key Method**: `GetSandboxType()` (line 32)\n  - Returns: `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox::kRenderer`\n- **Platform-Specific**: `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegateWin` for Windows\n  - Initializes sandbox policy via `InitializeConfig(sandbox::TargetConfig* config)`\n  - Configures PDF renderer and JIT settings\n  - Manages sandbox tags for policy selection\n\nImplementation: `content/browser/renderer_host/renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.cc`\n- `GetSandboxType()` at line 54-57 returns `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox::kRenderer`\n\n### 4. Sandbox Type Definitions and Profile Mappings\n\n**Main Definition**: `sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom`\n- **Enum**: `Sandbox` (lines 13-176)\n- **Renderer Entry** (line 62): `kRenderer` - \"Hosts untrustworthy web content. Blocks as much OS access as possible.\"\n- **Other Types**: `kGpu`, `kUtility`, `kAudio`, `kNetwork`, `kService`, `kNoSandbox`, etc.\n- **Platform-Specific Types**: `kIconReader`, `kMediaFoundationCdm`, `kPdfConversion` (Windows)\n\n**Type Utilities**: `sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h`\n- `IsUnsandboxedSandboxType(sandbox::mojom::Sandbox)` - check if unsandboxed\n- `SetCommandLineFlagsForSandboxType()` - configure process launch flags\n- `SandboxTypeFromCommandLine()` - parse sandbox type from arguments\n- `StringFromUtilitySandboxType()` - convert utility type to string\n\n## Security Architecture Chain\n\n1. **Launcher**: `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate::GetSandboxType()` determines sandbox type as `kRenderer`\n2. **Policy Selection**: Sandbox type maps to appropriate policy profile via `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox` enum\n3. **Windows Path**:\n   - `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegateWin::InitializeConfig()` applies policy\n   - Creates `PolicyBase` instance with restrictions from `TargetConfig` interface\n4. **Linux Path**:\n   - `RendererProcessPolicy` applies BPF restrictions\n   - Built on `BPFBasePolicy` and `BaselinePolicy`\n   - Uses seccomp-BPF for syscall filtering\n\n## Key Security Boundaries\n\n- **Windows**: Token levels, job objects, process mitigations, AppContainer isolation\n- **Linux**: seccomp-BPF syscall filtering, namespace isolation, broker process for privileged operations\n- **Common**: Renderer sandbox type enforces strongest restrictions possible for untrusted web content"
}

